      "body": "That might be the bug, but without the -rpcwait flag. But you misunderstand some things here: server=0 is not set in versions before 0.10. So it breaks compatibility, because old conf files don't contain server=0. Also an error like this is the responsibility of the person who writes the software, not the user. Blaming users for bad inputs is something you can allow yourself to do in your personal projects. It's like saying if I send -1 bitcoins the software crashes and that's the users fault. No, that's not how error handling and input validation works.\n",
